            <p class="lead">Airbnb is paying new Toronto hosts <strong>$1,000 CAD</strong> to list their home for the FIFA World Cup 2026. It's their biggest new host incentive ever, and it's available right now. With over <strong>300,000 visitors</strong> expected, hotel prices projected to double, and six matches at BMO Field between June 12 and July 2, this is the biggest short-term rental opportunity Toronto has ever seen.</p>
