            <li><strong>Principal residence only:</strong> You can only STR the home where you actually live. Investment properties don't qualify</li>
            <li><strong>Registration required:</strong> You need an STR number (STR-0000-XXXXXX) displayed on all listings. Fee: $390 for 2026</li>
            <li><strong>180-night annual limit:</strong> Applies to entire home rentals only. No limit on private rooms while you're home</li>
            <li><strong>$2M liability insurance:</strong> Required for all registered STR operators</li>
            <li><strong>Safety compliance:</strong> Smoke alarms, CO detectors, fire extinguishers</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="warning-box">
            <h4>Enforcement Is Tightened for 2026</h4>
            <p>Toronto has reduced the STR registration revocation process from 40 days to just 10 days. The city is cracking down on unregistered operators, especially ahead of the World Cup. Operating without registration can result in fines up to $100,000. Get registered now.</p>
          </div>

          <h2 id="mat-tax">The 8.5% MAT Tax Increase</h2>
