          <p>The city expects this increase to generate an additional $56.6 million. For hosts, this means:</p>

          <ul>
            <li>You must collect <strong>8.5% MAT</strong> on all bookings during this period</li>
            <li>Airbnb collects and remits MAT automatically on your behalf</li>
            <li>Rooms fully booked and paid before June 1, 2025 are exempt from the increase</li>
            <li>Partial prepayments or deposits do <strong>not</strong> qualify for the exemption</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Don't let the tax increase scare you. With hotel rates at $531/night average, guests are expecting to pay premium prices. The 8.5% MAT is a minor factor when your listing offers genuine value compared to a hotel room at double the price.</p>

